description: THE ANNOTATED SANDMAN VOL. 2 collects issues #21-39 of Neil Gaiman's THE SANDMAN, with annotations by Leslie Klinger (The Annotated Sherlock Holmes, The Annotated Dracula) to all the historical and literary references contained in the series. This edition includes the now legendary SEASON OF MISTS storyline, as well as A GAME OF YOU.
name: Volume Two

description:
What's going to happen when Charlie Brown takes his bowling-ball-shaped head down to the bowling alley? We won't reveal it here, but you can be sure it'll tickle your funny bone as the Peanuts gang closes out Volume 2! Ask your retailer about the Woodstock 1st appearance variant cover!

Note: This issue was released digitally one week before (11/21/12) the print release (11/28/12).
name: Food For Fraught; How to Draw Violet; Do the Math; From the Drawing Board; Classic Peanut Strips

description: Rachel and Jet will not stay dead. It's a mystery to the two BFFs, but they suspect it has something to do with a 10-year old serial killer and a witch who wants revenge on Manson, the little town with a wicked past. Critics are raving about Rachel Rising, and the series made the Horror Writers Association 2012 Recommended Reading List. Fear No Malus collects issues 7-12 of the Eisner Nominated series, written and drawn by Terry Moore.
name: Volume 2

description: Special sneak previews of JUSTICE LEAGUE #14, NIGHTWING #14, GREEN LANTERN: NEW GUARDIANS #14, CATWOMAN #14, and SUPERGIRL #14! Plus, previews of all the DC comics in stores this week!

This is not your typical 'How To Draw' book. Written for pros and amateurs alike, Terry Moore addresses the questions and challenges artists find after their art school education. Chapters include how to make art that sells, how to draw cartoons that work, how to draw expressions with even the simplest line and, Moore's forte, how to draw beautiful women. To wrap up, Moore details his step-by-step process making a comic book from drawing board to pdfs. This book is loaded with timely material geared toward the world of comics as it is today.
name: TPB

description: A team of misfits, who call themselves The Dare Detectives, have messed up on catching the bad guy again. They are comprised of Maria (the brains), Toby (the brawn), and Jojo (the jerkish rabbit). After getting their detective's license suspended, they go back to their landlord's restaurant, where something fishy is going on in the back... something to do with thuggish pandas. Set in Chinatown.
name: Part 1

description: The Dare Detectives find out the evil, thuggish pandas work for the crimelord, Mr. White, and have Uncle Chan to boot! After fighting to get him back, failing, and tearing Chinatown apart, it is revealed to them that there is a new crimelord in town...Madame Bleu...and she is using the services of the pandas, her monster pets, and the powers of freezing wind to get away with kidnapping Uncle Chan, as well as whatever else is up her sleeve.
name: Part 2

description: Epic battle ensues. The Dare Detectives have lost the fight...again....and are facing the police...again...and have torn Chinatown apart...again. But this time, they're not facing human police, but cops of the animal sort.
name: Part 3

description: It turns out the animal cops work directly for the mayor and Maria pulls one of them aside to ask a favor of him. She figures since Madame Bleu is using Mr. White's henchmen, then she's probably using other people he has worked with as well. She gets her favor to meet with Mr. White, who only speaks in rhyme and prose...he gives her a hint and they're off on the next part of their adventure.
name: Part 4

description: Set in Enderby City.Madame Bleu's hideout is in Mr. White's old burned up and flooded hideout. The Dare Detectives sneak in and, while the panda thugs are distracted by showgirls, they listen in and happen upon the stolen snowpeas...stolen from every noodle joint in town.
name: Part 5

description: The Panda thugs are lax in their methods of guarding the hideout, so The Dare Detectives slip right past them, causing a scuffle as they go against Madame Bleu's monster pets. Once past them, The Dare Detectives hide and see Madame Bleu preparing for a rather mysterious performance.
name: Part 6

description: Madame Bleu has revealed that Mr. White has warned her that The Dare Detectives and the cops would be coming...she prepared ahead of time for their appearance at her villain party. Furious George, the villain from the first chapter, is there working a machine that, coupled with Bleu's ring, would freeze the entire city. The Dare Detectives fight for it, but fail and end up trapped in a small storage room...frozen in. This is when they start to escape.
name: Part 7

description: Mme. Bleu dances on stage, before revealing her plan to enslave all of the villains. The villains run for it while she realizes that the ring is not being controlled. With no one controlling it, the ring tries to enslave everybody in capacity.
name: Part 8

description: Mme. Bleu is arrested, Uncle Chan stops Furious George and wins the reward money. He gives The Dare Detectives a break on their rent and they get their Detectives' license back. Another case closed.
name: Part 9

description: Reformed crook Maria Dare has assembled a team of misfits to crack the world's weirdest cases! They have brains, they have guts, but they don't have a clue! And in their first adventure, the Dare Detectives are finished! Rent's due and their license is suspended, but Dare's going-out-of-business festivities are interrupted by Madame Bleu, whose abominable snowmen pets are on a chef-stealing, radio-robbing, snowpea-swiping crime wave!
name: HC

volume.name: The Dare Detectives!: The Snow-Pea Plot

description: Time to reload: DOUBLE BARREL is back! Zander's hero HECK begins his horrific journey through the underworld, with faithful sidekick Elliot at his side... but they'll be reminded of some painful truths about themselves they'd rather not face. Meanwhile in Kevin's CRATER XV, the Royal Canadian Arctic Navy recruits Army Shanks to sneak aboard an ominous Soviet ship... before it launches a rocket into space! But can he focus on the mission when a pretty face from his past enters the picture? Plus BONUS short comics from both artists, Zander's tips for hand-lettering comics, your letters, and more! Saddle up with the Cannons for another dose of digital adventure! THIS is what comics are all about! THIS... is DOUBLE BARREL!

Mamas, hide your babies, 'cause the Cannons are back and firing on all cylinders! DOUBLE BARREL #3 is an incredible 116 pages of action, drama, and comic-book passion. Zander Cannon descends to the sixth chapter of HECK and finds it full of WRATH -- and some long-repressed memories! Kevin Cannon presents a huge chunk (over 50 pages) of CRATER XV -- the plot threads are multiplying like rabbits, as we're starting to see just how huge a mess Army Shanks has gotten himself into... Meanwhile both Cannons contribute a pile of bonus content, including Kevin's "Penny from the Front," Zander's hilarious "Master of Feng Shui," more True Tales of Jin (age 4), and a great essay from Zander about the storytelling masterclass that is STAR WARS. More fun than a barrel of monkeys? Of course it is -- it's DOUBLE BARREL!

Man the harpoons! A new DOUBLE BARREL has surfaced! First, Zander's HECK enters the city of Dis, the underworld's inner zone where the really bad folks dwell. In fact, some would say he belongs there... Meanwhile in Kevin's CRATER XV, Soviet Captain Sztab reveals his mad plan to take over the WORLD!! ...sort of. But how can he be stopped if our hero Shanks is sunk in a depressive stupor? PLUS: more "Penny from the Front," more adventures of Jin (age 4), and tips from Kevin on "sketch tourism"! All that AND the winners of our first contest? Better download DOUBLE BARREL #4 today!

Ready, aim, download! That's right, DOUBLE BARREL is back in action with a new issue! Zander's hero HECK faces the legendary Minotaur for his biggest fight yet, while the series continues to grow in emotional richness and venture into genuine tragedy. Then in Kevin's CRATER XV, Army's amnesiac crush Pravda is about to be carried off by the Russians, while he and the High Arctic League are trapped in an impregnable blockhouse... and Wendy is getting suspicious of her new friends. PLUS: Jin (age 4) threatens to spank trees on the butt, guest Steven Stwalley presents a zombie-walk gone wrong in "The Dead Living," and the Cannons team up for an exhaustive guide to surviving 24-Hour Comic Day!

Roll up, roll up! It's time to roll out another issue of DOUBLE BARREL! And boy, is this one a doozy. Zander's HECK saga hits its most incredible "holy #@$%" moment yet, as Heck and Elliott take a ride with Hell's horrific winged stinger-beast, Geryon! Meanwhile in Kevin's CRATER XV, Wendy learns more about Canada's space program, long abandoned -- or is it? -- and Shanks desperately races to keep his lost love Pravda from becoming a feast for a ferocious walrus! PLUS: more Penny from the Front, Jin (age 4) deals with getting sick, and Zander contributes a particularly insightful essay on using page layouts for effective storytelling.

The Pantheans have just prevailed in a bloody civil war. Things go quickly awry while attempting to imprison the traitorous Kronos and a multitude of monstrous intergalactic criminals. Now the crew of the Ulympea, led by Captain Suras, must do whatever it takes to stem a full-scale prison break. What happens next, however, is completely unexpected! What starts as a straight forward Sci-Fi story, soon takes twists and turns into a genre-bending epic that defies explanation.

Having crash-landed on ancient earth, over a thousand of miles apart, the Ulympeans and Tytans must adapt to life on their new "home." Added to this mix are the strange transformations they've undergone due to the Star Core's energies. And then there's the matter of the planet's primitive natives, and how they'll react to this alien presence. Are both groups as different as they think? Find out in "Reflections."

Three members of the Ulympean crew must track down the deadly Nemean before he can return to Kronos and reveal their location. They encounter one of the most advanced human civilizations along the way, and must save them from a mutual threat... with startling and long-lasting revelations and consequences.

Now armed with the knowledge of the Tytans' location, the female crew must use their abilities to infiltrate the very heart of the Tytan itself to recover the most important piece of technology... the Star Core itself. Twists and turns abound in the shocking conclusion to this tale.

Not only do we meet the Kronos' Royal Guard, we are treated to a flashback where we discover the truth behind the Star Core, the civil war that led to Kronos' fall from grace, and all of the circumstances that led up to events in Issue #1.

Temis and Frodaity's infiltration of the Tytan encampment is discovered, as they attempt to lead the last of the Tytan refugees to safety. Will they escape the clutches of Kronos, or will they be killed by the nefarious new "Guardians?"

Frodaity and Temis' fate is discovered as the first ever two-parter concludes in this issue. More revelations come to light as we meet up with some old friends and more plans are made for the coming war.

We meet Menes -- the human boy that will change the balance of power and affect the final fates of both the Ulympeans and Tytans... Plus the Guardians battle the Royal Guard for the right to rule the Tytans.

Siris shattered? What will happen to the Guardians, or the Ulympean plans for that matter? The startling conclusion to this epic two-parter as they try to piece together their plans as they crumble around them.

The Ulympean preparations are complete, however the mysterious hooded killer that's been stalking them has other ideas in mind. As they set to depart, he releases the winged Tauren, Gulganna, to cover his own nefarious plans.
The Egyptian War Saga kicks off with a bang, as the Ulympeans set sail. But with the startling revelation to Kronos, are the Ulympeans already sunk or just on a collision course for disaster?
INCURSION: The Ulympeans attempt to lure out Kronos.
TERMINUS: Here there be dragons!
FUSILLADE: Kronos attacks!
ASSAULT: Kronos attacked!

The Pantheans have just prevailed in a bloody civil war. Things go quickly awry while attempting to imprison the traitorous Kronos and a multitude of monstrous intergalactic criminals. What happens next, however, is completely unexpected! AFTERMATH: Suras is asked to leave the country!
PRODIGAL: A fan-favorite character returns from the dead... or does she?!
OBLIGATIONS: Hurk meets up with an old friend and receives some very bad news.
PREDATORS: Our heroines struggle to remain at the top of the food chain!
DARKNESS, MY OLD FRIEND: Our heroes battle an army of the undead!
PRESENT TENSE: A stunning look into the possible future (or is it present?) of the WAYWARD SONS universe!

Haydez of the Ulympeans discovers some very disturbing news, and is ultimately inspired to turn his sorrow into a source of joy as they bring their native "Holy Day" celebration to Earth in this revelation-packed issue with lasting ramifications for the series as a whole.
FREE holiday special! THE SOLSTICE: Kronos gets into the holiday sprit? with wildly unexpected results!

Ayumu and his housemates are getting on just as if they were an actual warm (or, in his case, cold) and loving family. And with Eu under threat from a mysterious nemesis known only as the King of Night, the motley crew is tighter than ever as they resolve to keep the shady necromancer safe. But when the resident vampire ninja, Sera, receives orders from home that threaten Eus well-being, will she turn her back on her new friends?!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 11: That's the Deadly Thunder Cross That Soars Through the Sky!
  • Chapter 12: How~! Does~! That~! Make~! Sense~!?
  • Chapter 13: Forget About Me And Get Cooking--!!
  • Chapter 14: ...When Sharing A Drink.
  • Chapter 15: So You're A Zombie
  • Chapter 16: Eu... Eu... Eucliwo--!
name: Vol. 3

description:
Its the big day for Nomiya, the tryouts for the Tokyo Lightnings professional basketball team. Nomiyas putting everything hes got into this moment, but will it be enough? Meanwhile, Takahashi is finally reaching a new stage in his rehabilitation, and a glimmer of his former life is coming backin the form of wheelchair basketball.

Contains chapters 61 to 66.
name: Vol. 11

description: Cecania arrives home from college, where she's immediately forced by her mother into working at her crazy brother Fairbanks' video game shop Sore Thumbs. All seems hopeless until she meets a young Iraq veteran named Sawyer and her best friend Harmony shows up out of nowhere.

Fairbanks and Harmony are introduced to Sawyer and his somewhat violent tiny polar bear Coleman, they face off with Mother over their plans, and they hang around the Greensworthington mansion. SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

Fairbanks sees Harmony naked (and it somehow results in him cross-dressing), Mother tries to seduce Sawyer, and the gang opens Sore Thumbs 2.0 for business and starts scaring the hell out of their many new customers. SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

Rondel Mayflower IV, Fairbanks' perverted nemesis/best friend, raps his way into Sore Thumbs for the first time! Meanwhile, Cecania and Sawyer break out of the back room! Can Cecania's ample assets increase sales? Is the Pope catholic? Yes, and yes. SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

Fairbanks plots to kill Rondel Mayflower IV and Sawyer mopes over Cecania, who mopes over the 2004 election results ... until she's invited to audition as a TV horror host! SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

Cecania's TV audition continues as she faces off against longtime rival Jasmine. Will she get the job? The answer to that question may change Sore Thumbs forever! SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!

While Fairbanks continues interviewing potential new Sore Thumbs employees, Cecania's adventures in the world of TV horror hosting take a surprisingly horrific turn, and celebrity blogger Wil Wheaton guest stars as "Crazy Homeless Guy." Plus, Harmony gets some Costume Party action as Chun-Li! SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!
